HEADWORD: Malabar
<hw>Mal"a*bar`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A region in the
western part of the Peninsula of India, between the mountains and the
sea.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Malabar nut</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>the seed of
an East Indian acanthaceous shrub, the <spn>Adhatoda Vasica</spn>,
sometimes used medicinally.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>malabar kino</ent>⟦br⟧
